    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The compass point towards the magnetic pole, to which a compass needle points, or generaly towards or in the direction of the pole on the earth's surface that lies on the earth's axis of rotation and at which the heavens appear to turn anticlockwise about a point directly overhead.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Situado hacia o en la dirección de, esa parte de la tierra o del cielo la cual, en el hemisferio norte, está más remoto del sol de mediodia. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
